{"id":"3956","name":"GPA Calculator (multiple grading scales)","tagline":"This is a GPA calculator to help you determine what your final GPA will be","icon":"ios13 c431817727 g59465","latest":"15238","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>This is a GPA calculator that incorporates multiple grading scales for easy GPA calculation prior to receiving your final report card.</p>\n<p>The GPA scales can be modified in the shortcut by changing the values inside the text items for the various sections (CollegePrep, Honors, or AP).</p>\n<p>When you run the shortcut, it asks you if it is a new term when you have a new list of classes, if you say 'yes', it will rebuild the class list based on your input.</p>\n<p>After this question is finished, it will then ask you (on the first run only), which type of class it is (CollegePrep, Honors, or AP). This determines the grading scale to be used.</p>\n<p>After this question is finished, it will then ask you (on the first run only), how many credits the respective class is worth.</p>\n<p>Once the above information is put into the shortcut, it saves this to your iCloud Drive files for future reference. It will then ask you what grades you received in the classes then calculate your GPA based on this information.</p>\n<p>The calculation used for this is ((Class1 GPA * Class1 Credits) + (Class2 GPA * Class2 Credits) + (Class3 GPA * Class3 Credits)) / TotalCredits for the term.</p>\n<p>New as of version 1.6: ability for temporary class list</p>\n<p>Contact with any questions or issues you may have</p>\n<p><img alt=\"mediakit\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/OiEeham.png\"></p>\n<hr>\n<p><img alt=\"GPACalcImg\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/8uMw1Ss.png\"> \n<img alt=\"GPACalcImg\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/forQuzU.png\">\n<img alt=\"GPACalcImg\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/cF7EQ5P.png\">\n<img alt=\"GPACalcImg\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/i3y6u50.png\">\n<img alt=\"GPACalcImg\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/zVVf6OZ.png\">\n<img alt=\"GPACalcImg\" src=\"https://i.im